WEBVTT

00:08.620 --> 00:13.700
Welcome to the Science Fiction Radio Show, a commentary on Science Fiction today.

00:14.520 --> 00:17.500
A presentation of the Permian Basin Science Fiction Association.

00:18.500 --> 00:19.720
And now your hosts.

00:27.160 --> 00:28.380
This is Daryl Lane.

00:28.680 --> 00:29.280
Keith Johnson.

00:29.280 --> 00:30.240
And David Carson.

00:30.420 --> 00:32.440
And the subject of this show will be First Contact.

00:33.600 --> 00:37.560
For over a century at least since H.G. Wells, War of the Worlds, contact with aliens has

00:37.560 --> 00:41.220
been one of the standard motifs of science fiction and certainly one of the most popular.

00:41.840 --> 00:45.400
There are of course a number of possibilities coming under the heading of alien contact.

00:45.920 --> 00:49.880
The aliens may be superior, we may be superior or there may be equality.

00:50.320 --> 00:52.820
The aliens might be friendly, hostile or indifferent.

00:53.940 --> 00:58.000
One of the most popular and fascinating possibilities of all is the story of First

00:58.000 --> 01:02.100
Contact, one of which the first meeting between humans and aliens is treated.

01:02.560 --> 01:06.720
Our present show will be the first of two on the subject of First Contact.

